  "text": "The Kubernetes API deprecation policy is enforced through a multi-layered system implemented in kubernetes/kubernetes. The core enforcement mechanisms are:\n\n1. **API Version Deprecation Detection and Warning Injection** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go):\n   - The `IsDeprecated()` function checks if an API version is deprecated by comparing the current Kubernetes version against APILifecycleDeprecated() versions implemented in each API type.\n   - The `RemovedRelease()` function extracts the removal version from objects implementing APILifecycleRemoved().\n   - The `WarningMessage()` function generates human-readable deprecation warnings that include the version when the API was deprecated, when it will be removed, and suggested replacements.\n   - The `MajorMinor()` function parses version information for comparison.\n\n2. **Removal Version Validation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/deleted_kinds.go):\n   - The `ResourceExpirationEvaluator` interface and implementation enforce removal version checks.\n   - The `ShouldServeForVersion()` method determines whether an API should continue to be served based on its removal version versus the current Kubernetes version.\n   - The `RemoveDeletedKinds()` method removes storage for API kinds that have reached their removal version, effectively preventing them from being served (with exceptions for alpha releases and emergency override).\n   - This uses the APILifecycleIntroduced and APILifecycleRemoved interfaces to determine version boundaries.\n\n3. **Minimum Supported API Version Validation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go):\n   - Storage version selection logic checks APILifecycleIntroduced() to ensure only API versions that were introduced in or before the current compatibility version are used.\n   - This prevents using storage versions for API types that didn't exist in earlier compatibility versions.\n\n4. **Warning Injection into Responses** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go):\n   - During endpoint registration in `registerResourceHandlers()`, deprecated APIs are identified and their deprecation status is tracked.\n   - The `deprecation.IsDeprecated()` function is called with the current Kubernetes version to determine deprecation status.\n   - Warnings are generated via `deprecation.WarningMessage()` and injected into responses.\n\n5. **Warning Recording and Deduplication** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/warning/warning.go and staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/warning.go):\n   - The `AddWarningsHandler()` function in warning.go adds warnings to request contexts.\n   - The `WithWarningRecorder()` filter in filters/warning.go manages warning deduplication and size limits (4KB total, 256 runes per warning) to ensure responses remain valid.\n   - Warnings are sent as HTTP Warning headers (RFC 7234 code 299) in API responses.\n\n6. **Metrics and Audit Logging** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go):\n   - The `deprecatedRequestGauge` metric tracks requests to deprecated APIs by group, version, resource, subresource, and removed_release version.\n   - The `MonitorRequest()` function records deprecated API usage.\n   - The `InstrumentRouteFunc()` wraps route handlers to capture deprecation information.\n   - Audit annotations are added with the removed_release version for compliance tracking.\n\n7. **API Installation and Enforcement** (pkg/controlplane/apiserver/apis.go):\n   - The `InstallAPIs()` method creates a `ResourceExpirationEvaluator` based on the current Kubernetes version.\n   - It calls `RemoveDeletedKinds()` on each API group to remove storage for APIs whose removal version has been reached.\n   - This prevents the API server from serving API versions that are no longer supported.\n\nThese files work together to implement the complete API deprecation policy: detecting deprecated API versions, warning users about their use, preventing removed API versions from being served, and recording telemetry for deprecation enforcement. The policy uses lifecycle interfaces (APILifecycleDeprecated, APILifecycleRemoved, APILifecycleIntroduced, APILifecycleReplacement) implemented via code generation on API types to drive the enforcement decisions."
}

